John Gilmore:

"[[Constellation]] will provide Distributed Computation capability using BOINC (Berkeley Open Interface for Network Computing). Basically Constellation is a series of idle computers with the BOINC software program installed on them (you can install it on yours too if you want to participate). To date there are 10,000 computers hosting the project."
